  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Access to Lifesaving and Sustaining Education to Droughts and Conflict Affected Out-of-School Children (Boys and Girls) in Balcad and Jowhar Districts, Middle Shabelle Region, Somalia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is designed to respond to the effects of the ongoing droughts on school-aged children in nine schools Balcad and Jowhar Districts of Middle Shabelle Region, Somalia.
The project targets schools that are the verge of closure due to lack of teachers&apos; incentives, and supply of basic teaching and learning. The situation is further exacerbated by lack of water and hunger that were set in by the droughts that are currently ravaging the country. The project targets nine existing schools, two in Balcad (in rural Balcad and one in town) and seven in rural villages of Jowhar. The schools which have a total enrollment of 3000 (40% girls) learners, will be targeted for water supply and school feeding program. Further, the project targets the schools for supply of teaching and learning material, payment of teachers&apos; incentives, teacher training, capacity development of CECs and hygiene promotion. The project aims to keep learners in schools and access basic education services at where they are rather than moving to other centers to seek for them same services and exert pressure on schools in urban centers like Balcad and Jowhar. The project will leverage existing school infrastructure in both districts and availability of trained teachers in Jowhar.   

To ensure the sustainability of the proposed intervention, Aid Vision will build the capacities of the schools&#x2019; Community Education Committees on school management, community mobilization and fund raising. Focus will be put on community engagement by the committees in order to raise resources internally to support school activities like payment of teachers and purchase of basic teaching and learning materials after end of the project life. As part of the Community Education Committee training, Aid Vision will help in community action planning which will focus on sustainability of schools.</narrative>
  </description>
